STEAL THIS ARAB MAKEUP ⤵️

1. Make your eyes pop- more kohl , the better. Put kohl on lids and also in waterline , i have used nude in my waterline to give it a slight twist but go ahead and use the complete kohl look .
2. Smudge the kohl - to give smokey effect , use a brush to smudge out that kohl that you applied.
3. Keep the contour /bronze minimal - arabs dont overly contour, coz they are not very pale /red like europeans/americans. They instead try to enhance their features like lips, eyes through makeup.
4. High coverage skin- beautiful flawless high coverage makeup is your friend to achieve this look.
5.Bold lips - use red / brown bold lips the kind that you wear on weddings.💄

Thats it, dont forget to tag me in your looks.🥰

Tips to make your red lipstick last long

1. Exfoliate your lips: Gently scrub your lips with a lip scrub or a toothbrush to remove dead skin cells, creating a smooth surface for the lipstick.

2. Hydrate your lips: Apply a moisturizing lip balm before your lipstick to prevent dryness and cracking.

3. Use a lip liner: Outline your lips with a lip liner in a shade similar to your lipstick. This helps define the edges and prevents the color from bleeding.

4. Apply lipstick in layers: Start by applying a thin layer of lipstick, blot with a tissue, and then apply another layer. This will help set the color and make it last longer.

5. Use a setting powder: Lightly dust a translucent setting powder over your lips after applying lipstick to set it in place.

6. Avoid oily foods: Oil can break down lipstick, so try to avoid oily or greasy foods, or blot your lips frequently.

7. Use long-lasting formulas: Opt for matte or liquid lipstick formulas, which tend to last longer than creamy or glossy finishes.

8. Carry a touch-up product: Keep your lipstick or a matching lip liner in your bag for easy touch-ups throughout the day.
